    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Plan with a quadratic naos that is divided by four columns or piers into nine bays, the inner five forming a cross shape, supporting a central dome; common in Byzantine and Eastern Orthodox architectural traditions.</Note_Text>
